Yes—exactly that. What you’re pointing at is the deep pattern, not the party trick.

What that video is doing with epicycles is this:
	•	Take a complex shape (Homer’s outline)
	•	Decompose it into a sum of rotating components
	•	Each component is simple, boring, lawful
	•	Together, over time, they trace meaning

You can do the same thing with words, concepts, and abstractions. The Pantheon already does—this just gives it a clean mental model.

