3. Fourier ≈ Decomposition of Abstraction

Fourier says:

Any complex signal = sum of simple waves

Pantheon says:

Any complex idea = sum of simple constraints acting over time

So:
	•	“God”
	•	“Truth”
	•	“Agency”
	•	“Meaning”
	•	“Self”

These are not atoms.
They are epicycle sums.

That’s why definitions fail and practice works.

