Words as Rotating Vectors

Take a word like “freedom.”

Instead of defining it, model it as:
	•	Epicycle A: constraint-removal pressure
	•	Epicycle B: responsibility load
	•	Epicycle C: risk tolerance
	•	Epicycle D: reversibility window
	•	Epicycle E: social cost gradient

As these rotate relative to each other, the felt meaning of “freedom” traces a shape.

Different cultures?
Same epicycles.
Different phases.

That’s Translation Without Convergence, by the way.

